==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*lubo'', from Indo-European ''*leubh-''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[luve]], Old High German [[luba]], Gothic ''(𐌱𐍂𐍉𐌸𐍂𐌿) 𐌻𐌿𐌱𐍉'' ‘(brotherly) love’.

